page.title: 01AISBY
page.content: This is an arable farming area of South Lincolnshire with less than 100 people living in it.The largest settlement is in a small hamlet called Aisby which is in the north of the block.There are no amenities and no industry and only 1 main road,the A52, crosses the block. The limestone landscape shows features of former glaciation during the last Ice Age. There is evidence of former Romano- British occupation. The land to the south of the A52 is mainly owned by 1 large estate and is farmed by the estate-financed company and feq of the local inhabitants have jobs on the land.
